com.camerontec.catalys.util.data

Interface ITagValue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, Comparable<ITagValue>, IValue, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    StandardTagValue

    public interface ITagValue
extends IValue, Comparable<ITagValue>
    Holds an int tag and an IValue object.

    Message summary:

    • Inherits all the IValue methods - see summary for IValue
    • getTag() and setTag(int)
    • getValue() and setValue(IValue)
    Note that this interface extends Comparable. Implementations are expected to compare ITagValue's by tag number, in ascending order.

      • copyFrom

        void copyFrom(ITagValue other)
        Copies tag/value from another ITagValue object into this one.

        Note that no object creation occurs here unless bytes are being copied and this object's byte array is not long enough.

        Parameters:
        other - ITagValue whose value is to be copied.

      • setValue

        void setValue(IValue value)
        Sets (copies) the value associated with this ITagValue.

        Note that the contents of the value are copied rather than just assigning a reference to the given value. The value object of an ITagValue cannot be changed once it is created. Only its contents can be changed.

        Parameters:
        value - - Value associated with this tag value.
